      "writtenOn": "2018-04-09T22:39:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the best case Sk2f::abs() and std::abs() are identical, so I\u0027d favor Sk2f::abs() for it being under our control.  It oughta be an instruction or two at most, but I could imagine std::abs() implemented in all sorts of silly ways.\n\nmaxValue() is sometimes worse.  Rule of thumb is you should never cross vector lanes if you don\u0027t have to.  Don\u0027t do any operations on them that you can\u0027t do on scalars.  (This includes allTrue() and anyTrue().)",
      "parentUuid": "c14ebbc1_59fba041",
