      "writtenOn": "2018-04-09T22:39:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looks fine to me.  Is there any part in particular that has you worried?\n\nWhat exactly is the matrix and the vector here?\n\n  | p1.x - p0.x  p1.y - p0.y |   | l.y |\n  | p2.x - p0.x  p2.y - p0.y | * | l.x |\n\n?\n\nHave you learned how to tag this up and analyze with IACA yet?  It\u0027s static analysis, but usually pretty good for this sort of thing.  https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/intel-architecture-code-analyzer\n\nIf you like, I think you should be able to store directly into the transposed vectors:\n\n   Sk2f T[2];\n   Sk2f::Store2(T, p1-p0, p2-p0);\n   Sk2f d \u003d T[0]*l[1] - T[1]*l[0];\n\nIt\u0027s probably all the same underneath either way.",
